3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a new construction method for cyclic codes, which involves algorithmic techniques and may be of interest to researchers in the field of data structures and algorithms. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - Although the paper does not directly deal with social and information networks, the topic of error-correcting codes is relevant to network communication and data transmission, which may be of interest to researchers in this sub-category. 
5. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) - The paper involves numerical data analysis and provides a new method for estimating the minimal distance of cyclic codes, which may be of interest to researchers in numerical analysis.
